The paper deals with the problem of adapting a gaze estimator trained on synthetic data to real-world data. This involves using deep learning techniques such as generative adversarial networks (GANs) and unsupervised domain adaptation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.GR (Graphics), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
